goals.question: What is the relationship between life expectancy and income?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of life expectancy vs income
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is a correlation between income and life expectancy. It will also help us identify any outliers or patterns in the data.

goals.question: What is the distribution of income across different countries?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of income by country
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the range of income levels across different countries. It will also help us identify any countries with particularly high or low income levels.

goals.question: How has life expectancy changed over time?
goals.visualization: Line chart of life expectancy over time
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if life expectancy has been increasing or decreasing over time. It will also help us identify any trends or patterns in the data.

goals.question: What is the distribution of health spending across different countries?
goals.visualization: Box plot of health spending by country
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the range of health spending levels across different countries. It will also help us identify any countries with particularly high or low health spending levels.

goals.question: Is there a correlation between health spending and life expectancy?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of health spending vs life expectancy
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is a correlation between health spending and life expectancy. It will also help us identify any outliers or patterns in the data.

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_csv('gapminder-health-income.csv')

# Convert year to datetime
data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')

# Create scatter plot
sns.scatterplot(x='income', y='life_expectancy', hue='year', data=data)

# Set chart title
plt.title('What is the relationship between life expectancy and income?')

# Rotate x-axis labels
plt.xticks(rotation=45)

# Show legend
plt.legend(title='Year', loc='center left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0.5))

# Show plot
plt.show()
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_csv('gapminder-health-income.csv')

# Bar chart of income by country
sns.set_style("whitegrid")
sns.set_palette("husl")
sns.barplot(x="country", y="income", data=data)
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.title("What is the distribution of income across different countries?")
plt.xlabel("Country")
plt.ylabel("Income")
plt.show()
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

data = pd.read_csv('gapminder-health-income.csv')

data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')
data = data.dropna(subset=['life_expectancy'])

sns.set_style("whitegrid")
sns.set_palette("husl")

chart = sns.lineplot(x='year', y='life_expectancy', data=data)
chart.set_title('How has life expectancy changed over time?', wrap=True)
chart.set_xlabel('Year')
chart.set_ylabel('Life Expectancy')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)

plt.show()
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

data = pd.read_csv('gapminder-health-income.csv')

sns.set(style="whitegrid")
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 10))

sns.boxplot(x="Country", y="Health", data=data, ax=ax, palette="Set3")
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.title("What is the distribution of health spending across different countries?")

plt.show()
```
